==Russian==
{{swp|ru:}}

===Etymology===
From {{af|ru|вода́<t:water>|-ка<pos:diminutive suffix>}}. {{etydate|1533}}, at first only in medical context; the beverage sense appeared in the 17th century and became widespread in the 19th, displacing {{m|ru|хле́бное вино́|lit=grain wine}} by the early 20th century. The beverage sense is probably a {{semantic loan|ru|pl|wódka|nocap=1}}, which, per Brückner, in turn may be a {{semantic loan|ru|ML.|aqua vitae|nocap=1}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{ru-IPA|во́дка}}
